cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses a new approach to citation ranking in bibliometrics, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information, including bibliographic data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as it deals with the retrieval of information from large collections of data, including bibliographic databases. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as it deals with the social and ethical implications of technology, including the impact of bibliometrics on academic evaluation. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as it deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on information dissemination, which is relevant to citation analysis. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but it deals with the security and privacy of information, which is relevant to the protection of bibliographic data.
